it’s just that billie has more photo galleries than nia and it worse when you had a crush on one of them and the other only derived from the crush you had on the previous one due to having similar facial features. which makes it a little harder… a little… i’m fine.

summary: Today in bizarre discourse I accidentally stumbled upon, apparently there are Doctor Who fans who think Ten not seeing Billie...
body:
Today in bizarre discourse I accidentally stumbled upon, apparently there are Doctor Who fans who think Ten not seeing Billie Piper as the Moment in The Day of the Doctor was disrespectful to Davies’ era for not featuring a loving reunion?

For who those who don’t know why that choice was made or for any reason feel bitter about it, this was the reasoning:

“I thought the story of Rose, which was beautiful, was done. I didn’t want to add to it, and I didn’t feel comfortable adding to it, really. That was always Russell [T Davies]’s story. But we did want Billie. And I liked the idea of bringing back the Bad Wolf version. The way Russell ended it in “The End of Time,” by just sort of looping it around, was perfect. I didn’t want to stick another bit of it in. That would be wrong. I just wanted to get Billie Piper, one of the absolute heroes of Doctor Who, back in the show, but without interfering with the story of Rose Tyler. I just thought I might spoil something. I might trip over my bootlaces doing that.”

- Steven Moffat (x)
